cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper deals with natural language processing and neural network models for capturing semantic relationships between concepts in the biomedical domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval and machine learning techniques, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) respectively. Additionally, the use of embedding vectors and deep learning models suggests a possible fit in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Deep Learning).
